      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "Run the game and observe the effect.\r\nThe camera follows
          the player at a 1:1 ratio (the camera will immediately jump to the player\u2019s
          position).\r\nWe can do better than this. In the past, the only solution
          was to write code for the Main Camera to follow the position of the player
          (every frame moving the camera position closer to the target position using
          <doc>Vector3.MoveTowards</doc> and other functions). Such code tends to
          expand out monumentally once you try to add additional factors such as
          the bounds of the entire game world, or zooming on the player or points
          of interest.\r"
